  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "7. the men of Israel said unto the Hivites, Peradventure ye dwell among us—The answer of the Israelites implied that they had no discretion, that their orders were imperative, and that if the strangers belonged to any of the native tribes, the idea of an alliance with them was unlawful since God had forbidden it (Ex 23:32; 34:12; De 7:2).",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
