  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 7.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And the men of Israel said.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The Keri here has the singular number instead of the Chethibh plural, in consequence of Israel speaking of itself collectively in the word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "בְּקִרְבִּי",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and of the singular ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "אִישׁ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". But this last with a plural verb, as a noun of multitude, occurs in the historical books in places too numerous to mention. See, for instance, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 14:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", just as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "עַם",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " in many passages, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "e.g.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 18:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", is the nominative to a plural verb. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The Hivites",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (see note on ver. 3). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Peradventure ye dwell among us, and how can we make a league with you?",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " This was strictly forbidden in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 23:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 34:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 7:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", in reference to neighbouring nations, on account of the polluting influence their example had exercised (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 25:1-3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and was sure to exercise, as the subsequent history of the Israelites from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " onwards, proves. Joshua 9:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
